==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outcast
<hw>Out"cast`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>utkasta</ets> to cast out.]</ety> <def>Cast out; degraded.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Outcast</xex>, rejected.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outcast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outcast
<hw>Out"cast`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is cast out
or expelled; an exile; one driven from home, society, or country; hence,
often, a degraded person; a vagabond.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Lord . . . gathereth together the <qex>outcasts</qex> of
Israel.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. cxlvii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A quarrel; a contention.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outcasting</ent>⟦br⟧
